    "# Step 6: Filter out very short noisy fragments\n",
    "\n",
    "SEC HTML extraction sometimes leaves fragments like:\n",
    "\n",
    "* `Item 1`\n",
    "* `Table of Contents`\n",
    "* page artifacts\n",
    "* isolated headers\n",
    "\n",
    "So apply a light sentence-quality filter.\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "def is_valid_sentence(text: str, min_chars: int = 25) -> bool:\n",
    "    text = str(text).strip()\n",
    "\n",
    "    if len(text) < min_chars:\n",
    "        return False\n",
    "\n",
    "    if text.lower() in {\"table of contents\", \"item 1\", \"item 1a\", \"item 7\"}:\n",
    "        return False\n",
    "\n",
    "    return True\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Apply it:\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "df_sentences[\"is_valid\"] = df_sentences[\"sentence_text\"].apply(is_valid_sentence)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_sentences_clean = df_sentences[df_sentences[\"is_valid\"]].copy()\n",
    "df_sentences_clean.drop(columns=[\"is_valid\"], inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(df_sentences_clean.shape)\n",
